    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26507.2.3" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Piston Rings</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Faulty rings cannot always be detected by visual inspection. Therefore, whenever a piston is
                    removed from a cylinder, replace the piston rings.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect new piston rings for cleanliness.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before installing new piston rings on piston, check gap for each ring as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Push piston ring down into cylinder bore. Make sure the piston ring is square with
                    cylinder wall. An inverted piston head can be used to push piston ring to desired location of
                    measurement (usually at the top of the piston ring travel).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Use a feeler gauge to measure gap between ends of each piston ring.</para>
                <figure id="e300814" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figJ04/J04007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Piston ring end gap clearance in cylinder bore</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Piston ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler gauge</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If gap does not meet specifications, select another ring or recheck cylinder bore wear.
                    See
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_325.xml" xrefid="E3008A">Specifications
                        <xref refid="E3008A"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
